The Rust GUI (`ontrack-gui`) is a native desktop application built with [egui](https://github.com/emilk/egui) via the [eframe](https://github.com/emilk/egui/tree/master/crates/eframe) framework.

## Features

- Native GPU-accelerated rendering (OpenGL/Vulkan/Metal)
- TDS Telecom branding
- File picker via `rfd` (native file dialogs)
- Background route computation via `crossbeam-channel`
- Persistence of settings between sessions

## System Requirements

### Linux
Requires windowing system libraries. On NixOS these are provided by the flake. On other distros:

```bash
# Debian/Ubuntu
sudo apt install libxkbcommon-dev libgl-dev libwayland-dev \
  libx11-dev libxcursor-dev libxi-dev libxrandr-dev \
  libvulkan-dev libfontconfig-dev libfreetype-dev

# Fedora
sudo dnf install libxkbcommon-devel mesa-libGL-devel wayland-devel \
  libX11-devel libXcursor-devel libXi-devel libXrandr-devel \
  vulkan-loader-devel fontconfig-devel freetype-devel
```

### macOS
Requires Xcode command-line tools. AppKit, Metal, and CoreGraphics frameworks are used automatically.

### Windows
Works out of the box with the MSVC toolchain. The `x86_64-pc-windows-gnu` cross-target can build Windows binaries from Linux, but GUI support requires manual setup.

## Running

```bash
# Via Nix
nix run .#ontrack-gui

# Build from source
cd ontrack-rs
cargo run -p ontrack-gui --release
```

## Architecture

The GUI uses egui's immediate-mode pattern:

1. **Main thread**: Runs the egui render loop, handles input, draws UI
2. **Background thread**: Performs geocoding, matrix computation, and solving
3. **Channel**: `crossbeam-channel` sends results from background to UI

This prevents the UI from freezing during long operations.

## Dependencies

```toml
eframe      = { version = "0.27", features = ["default_fonts", "persistence"] }
egui        = "0.27"
egui_extras = { version = "0.27", features = ["image"] }
image       = { version = "0.25", features = ["png"] }
rfd         = "0.14"
crossbeam-channel = "0.5"
open        = "5"
```
